cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper is about sequential recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses collaborative relations among users and items, which falls under social and information networks (cs.SI) and recommender systems (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a new model for sequential recommendation, which could also be relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it involves modeling cross-neighbor relations.
